Thanks for answering me, because I was wondering if the &quot;I love yous&quot; were something characteristic of just the entities I&#39;m talking to (maybe even the same entity over and over again), or characteristic of most entities in general -- like they have different priorities on what constitutes an important message once a person has died.  For instance, my father I&#39;m certain would&#39;ve told me to move the trees I&#39;d planted over the septic tank, but would&#39;ve never said &quot;I love you.&quot;  Maybe once he&#39;s dead, everything looks different to him?  (That&#39;s providing I&#39;m really talking to dead people, which I&#39;m starting to wonder about.)

I&#39;m also noticing a tendency for the names I&#39;m getting lately to be Biblical:  Joseph and Michael have come through strongly, and I have no clue who they are.  Maybe they make a name in order to talk to me?

I&#39;ve also been reading more about how there can be seemingly different groups of entities competing to talk:

http://othersidecommunications.com/modules.php?name=Content&pa=showpage&pid=11

I witnessed this, I think, myself when my uncle came through (giving supporting evidence that it truly was him) and I also heard someone say &quot;Get away from me.&quot;  So maybe our dead relatives are indeed there, but other entities, wanting to hog the spotlight, get in the way or skew what our dead relatives say?  Just a thought.



